# Hardware Driver Rules

## CAN2USB Protocol
The RobStride CAN2USB debugger (CH340, VID:PID 1A86:7523) speaks an AT-framed binary protocol. NOT SLCAN, NOT robotell. Frame format:

```
TX/RX: 'A' 'T' [4B wire_id] [1B len] [data...] '\r' '\n'
wire_id = (29-bit arb_id << 3) | 0x04, big-endian
```

The `robstride` Rust crate's `CH341Transport` handles this protocol natively. No custom framing code needed.

## RS03 Motor Specs
- 60 N·m peak / 20 N·m rated torque
- 50 rad/s max speed
- 9:1 planetary gearbox, 880g
- 48V nominal (currently running at 24V on bench)
- CAN 2.0B extended frames (29-bit ID), 1 Mbps

## Motor API Pattern
`Motor` struct in `src/motor.rs` wraps the `robstride` crate's `Protocol` and `CH341Transport`. Multiple motors on the same CAN bus share one transport instance. The Rust crate's `Transport` trait is async (tokio), so motor methods are `async fn`. Use `impl Drop` for automatic disable on cleanup.

## Important Gotchas
- The `robstride` Rust crate is async — all I/O goes through tokio
- Multiple motors MUST share one `CH341Transport` instance on the same bus
- Always disable motors on Drop / cleanup to prevent runaway
- MotorStudio must be CLOSED before the program can open COM5
